                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p>\n                <add>יצחק בחור וטוב אשר נסעת</add>\n            </p>\n            "
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3tm72m44/canvas/p2"
                },
                {
                  "id": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3tm72m44/manifest/annotation/p2",
                  "type": "Annotation",
                  "motivation": "commenting",
                  "body": {
                    "type": "TextualBody",
                    "value": "\n            <p>you will receive the Sefer Torah before<lb/>\n                <date>Passover</date>.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(1)\">I hope to receive your answer.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\">Your friend <sic>an</sic> Servant,</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\"><persName role=\"author\">Elijah</persName>, son of\n                    <persName>Moses</persName>, Scribe.</p>\n            <p rend=\"indent(2)\"><persName role=\"author\">E. M. Holzman</persName>.</p>\n            <p>I request an immediate answer, in<lb/> order that I may justify myself; if<lb/> not\n                    <del>you will receive the Sefer Torah only</del> then we will be able to see\n                each other<lb/> only after <date>Passover</date>, when, God willing,<lb/> I shall be\n                in <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>. At that time<lb/> I hope, I shall be able to\n                make my<lb/> enemies, “look like the rim of a pot,”<lb/> and God will grant you\n                goodness and<lb/> life and that you will celebrate the<lb/>\n                <date>passover</date> in joy.</p>\n        </body>\n    </text>\n</TEI>\n"
                  },
                  "target": "https://colenda.library.upenn.edu/items/ark:/81431/p3tm72m44/canvas/p2"
                }
              ]
            }
